headline: Nvidia Stock Slips. What’s Moving the AI Chip Maker.
summary: Nvidia stock was down early on Friday, as investors digest news about how its chips were used by a Chinese start-up to train a cutting-edge artificial-intelligence model.  Nvidia  shares were down 3.4% at $135.12 in early trading.  Nvidia shares have bounced back from lows of less than $130 as investors judge how quickly the company can ramp up sales of its Blackwell AI chips.

headline: 2 Artificial Intelligence (AI) ETFs to Confidently Buy Heading Into 2025
summary: Artificial intelligence (AI) was the dominant theme in the stock market in 2024.  There were standout performances from select AI chip stocks, AI software stocks, and even energy stocks, as power-hungry data centers sent electricity demand soaring.  As a result, it is likely to remain the leading story in the stock market throughout 2025.
